Description: Thin gold wire of square cross-section irregularly twisted and bent in two.
Findspot: Found/Acquired: Tell Dafana, From the denuded surface of the site or the neighbourhood ? (?)
Curator's comments: Provenance not specified in the Museum register, but probably from Tell Nabasha according to the context of the item in the list, or possibly from Tell Dafana. If from Tell Dafana, it resembles the wire used for making links of a chain, such as in London, BM, EA 18279 and 18265, or coiled around an ear-ring, such as EA 18262. See also the twisted wire EA 18276.
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.84, p.186, pl.28)
